text: Stung Treng () is a city in Cambodia. It is the capital of Stung Treng Province in Cambodia. As of 2009, Stung Treng had 29,665 people. == Geography == Stung Treng is on the Sesan River near the Mekong River. It is from Phnom Penh and south of the Cambodia-Laos border.
